===Etymology===
In 1811, an Old Fogey was a nickname for an invalid, wounded soldier; derived from the {{der|en|fr|fougueux||fierce or fiery}}.<ref>{{R:1811 Vulgar Tongue|fogey|url=https://books.google.de/books?id=aadWAAAAcAAJ&hl=it&pg=PT93#v=onepage&q&f=false}}</ref> Alternatively, compare {{m|en|fogey}}.

